var __index = {"config":{"lang":["en"],"separator":"[\\s\\-,:!=\\[\\]()\"/]+|(?!\\b)(?=[A-Z][a-z])|\\.(?!\\d)|&[lg]t;","pipeline":["stopWordFilter"]},"docs":[{"location":"index.html","title":"Django SSO Auth","text":"<p>Welcome to the documentation for <code>django_sso_auth</code>, a Django package designed to provide seamless Single Sign-On (SSO) authentication using Okta. This package aims to simplify the integration of Okta SSO into your Django applications, ensuring secure and efficient user authentication and session management.</p>"},{"location":"index.html#overview","title":"Overview","text":"<p><code>django_sso_auth</code> is a comprehensive solution for integrating Okta SSO into Django projects. It provides the necessary tools and configurations to authenticate users via Okta, manage user sessions, and ensure secure access to your Django admin and API endpoints.</p>"},{"location":"index.html#key-features","title":"Key Features","text":"<ul> <li>Okta SSO Integration: Easily integrate Okta SSO for user authentication.</li> <li>Custom Authentication Backends: Provides custom authentication backends for Django and Django REST Framework.</li> <li>Token Verification: Securely verify JWT tokens issued by Okta.</li> <li>User Management: Automatically create and manage user accounts based on Okta claims.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"index.html#installation","title":"Installation","text":"<p>To install <code>django_sso_auth</code>, run the following command:</p> <pre><code>$ pip install git+https://github.com/homeservefinance/django_sso_auth\n\n---&gt; 100%\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"index.html#configuration","title":"Configuration","text":"<p>Update your <code>settings.py</code> with the necessary Okta settings:</p> <pre><code>INSTALLED_APPS = [\n    'django_sso_auth', # Add at the top of the list if you want to override the default admin login page\n    # other apps\n]\n\nSSO_AUTH = {\n    'AUTH_API_CLIENT_ID': 'your-okta-api-client-id',\n    'AUTH_ADMIN_CLIENT_ID': 'your-okta-admin-client-id',\n    'AUTH_API_CLIENT_SECRET': 'your-okta-api-client-secret',\n    'AUTH_DOMAIN': 'your-okta-domain',\n    'AUTH_ALGORITHMS': ['RS256'],\n    'OAUTH_CLASS': 'authlib.integrations.django_client.OAuth',\n}\n\n# Add the authentication backends\nAUTHENTICATION_BACKENDS = [\n    'django_sso_auth.admin.backend.OktaBackend',\n    # other backends\n]\n\n# Add the DRF authentication class\nREST_FRAMEWORK = {\n    'DEFAULT_AUTHENTICATION_CLASSES': (\n        'django_sso_auth.drf.authentication.OktaJWTAuthentication',\n        # other classes\n    ),\n}\n</code></pre> <p>Update your <code>urls.py</code> to include the <code>django_sso_auth</code> URLs:</p> <pre><code>from django.urls import path, include\n\nurlpatterns = [\n    path('', include('django_sso_auth.urls')),\n    # other URLs\n]\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"index.html#quick-start","title":"Quick Start","text":"<p>WIP</p>"},{"location":"index.html#license","title":"License","text":"<p>This project is licensed under the MIT License.</p> <p>For more detailed information on how to use <code>django_sso_auth</code>, please refer to the tutorial and features sections.</p>"},{"location":"changelog.html","title":"Changelog","text":"<p>All notable changes to the Django SSO Auth project will be documented in this file.</p> <p>The format is based on Keep a Changelog.</p>"},{"location":"changelog.html#unreleased","title":"Unreleased","text":""},{"location":"changelog.html#added","title":"Added","text":"<ul> <li>Initial project setup.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"changelog.html#001-yyyy-mm-dd","title":"0.0.1 - YYYY-MM-DD","text":""},{"location":"changelog.html#added_1","title":"Added","text":"<ul> <li>First release of Django SSO Auth.</li> <li>Basic notification functionality.</li> <li>Initial documentation.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"contributing.html","title":"Contributing to Django SSO Auth","text":"<p>We welcome all contributors to Django SSO Auth! Whether you're thinking of fixing bugs, adding new features, or improving documentation, your contributions are much appreciated.</p>"},{"location":"contributing.html#how-can-i-contribute","title":"How Can I Contribute?","text":"<p>There are many ways you can contribute:</p> <ul> <li>Bug Reports: If you found a bug, please create an issue in our GitHub repository explaining the problem and how to reproduce it. </li> <li>Feature Requests: If you have a great idea to improve Django SSO Auth, feel free to create an issue describing your idea.  </li> <li>Code Contribution: If you want to get your hands dirty with our code, you can fork our repository, make your changes and create a pull request.</li> <li>Documentation: You can help improve our documentation, making it more comprehensive, correcting errors, or creating tutorials.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"contributing.html#code-contribution-guidelines","title":"Code Contribution Guidelines","text":"<ul> <li>Ensure your code is formatted according to PEP 8.</li> <li>Write tests for the features you add or bugs you fix.</li> <li>Update the documentation if necessary.</li> <li>Make sure your code passes all the tests before submitting a pull request.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"faqs.html","title":"Frequently Asked Questions","text":"<p>This page contains answers to some of the most commonly asked questions about Django SSO Auth.</p> <p>List questions and their answers here.</p>"},{"location":"components/additional/index.html","title":"WIP","text":""},{"location":"components/core/index.html","title":"WIP","text":""},{"location":"features/bearer_token.html","title":"WIP","text":""},{"location":"features/sso.html","title":"WIP","text":""},{"location":"tutorial/step_1.html","title":"Step 1: Setting Up","text":"<p>This tutorial will walk you through the process of setting up Django SSO Auth in your Django application.</p>"},{"location":"tutorial/step_1.html#what-youll-need","title":"What You'll Need","text":"<p>List of prerequisites.</p>"},{"location":"tutorial/step_1.html#instructions","title":"Instructions","text":"<p>Step-by-step instructions with code snippets.</p>"},{"location":"tutorial/step_1.html#next-steps","title":"Next Steps","text":"<p>What the reader should do next, usually directing them to the next tutorial.</p>"}]}